                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The letters show the beginnings of a shift towards the later cursive style, with extended serifs on the A and M, T tending to be narrow with upward sloping head, E likewise tall, narrow, with top stroke sloping upwards. Interpuncts, sometimes in the form of hedera, used between all words except after Calbentius</p>
